A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing March 29 to April 5, 2025, as Georgia Community-Based Doula Week; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, community-based doulas provide continuous support to mothers during labor
4 and delivery, helping them cope with the physical and mental demands of giving birth; and
5 WHEREAS, drawing on their specialized training and lived experience to guide birthing
6 persons through labor and delivery, community-based doulas provide emotional support and
7 physical comfort that enhance the childbirth experience for the entire family; and
8 WHEREAS, community-based doulas have a commonality with the birthing person, which
9 improves outcomes for underserved communities; and
10 WHEREAS, community-based doulas work with medical staff, including doctors, midwives,
11 and nurses, to provide informational support to all birthing people they serve and help with
12 their transition to parenthood; and
13 WHEREAS, community-based doulas remove barriers to care by meeting families prenatally
14 and postpartum in the home as well as work to address maternal health disparities; and
